%N A397855 Decimal expansion of Gamma(5/3)/(3*Pi/2)^(1/3).
%C A397855 Let N(n) be the number of vertices of the convex hull of n points independently and uniformly selected at random in a disk. Then, as n tends to infinity, the distribution of (N(n) - 2*Pi*c1*n^(1/3))/sqrt(2*Pi*c2*n^(1/3)) converges to the standard normal distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation 1, where c1 is this constant and c2 = A397856 (Groeneboom, 1988; Finch and Hueter, 2004).
%C A397855 Let d(n) denotes the fraction of the area in the disk that is outside the convex hull. Then, as n tends to infinity, the distribution of of (d(n) - 2*Pi*c1*n^(1/3))/sqrt(2*Pi*(c1/3+c2)*n^(-5/3)) converges to the standard normal distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation 1.
%H A397855 Steven Finch and Irene Hueter, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/4140385">Random convex hulls: a variance revisited</a>, Advances in Applied Probability, Vol. 36, No. 4 (2004), pp. 981-986. See p. 981.
%H A397855 Claude Godrèche and Jean-Marc Luck, <a href="http://doi.org/10.1088/1742-5468/ad65e5">On sequences of convex records in the plane</a>, Journal of Statistical Mechanics: Theory and Experiment, Vol. 2024, No. 9 (2024), Article 093208; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.17309">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:2404.17309 [cond-mat.stat-mech], 2024.
%H A397855 Piet Groeneboom, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00342231">Limit theorems for convex hulls</a>, Probability theory and related fields, Vol. 79, No. 3 (1988), pp. 327-368. See p. 361, eq. (3.34).
%H A397855 Piet Groeneboom, <a href="https://www.nieuwarchief.nl/serie5/pdf/naw5-2023-24-3-172.pdf">Convex hulls</a>, Nieuw Archief voor Wiskunde, Vol. 24 (2023), pp. 172-176.
%F A397855 Equals 2^(7/3) * Pi^(2/3) / (3^(11/6) * Gamma(1/3)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jul 13 2026
